  "title": "Netflix Q4 2025 Earnings Call",
  "datetime": "2026-01-21T21:00:00Z",
  "period": "CY2025_Q4",
  "location": "Los Gatos, CA",
  "url": "https://ir.netflix.net/",
  "turns": [
    {
      "speaker_id": "greg-peters",
      "speaker_name": "Greg Peters",
      "speaker_role": "Co-CEO",
      "timestamp": "00:01:00",
      "text": "Q4 2025 capped a remarkable year. We ended with 327 million paid subscribers — exceeding our 320 million year-end target. Full-year operating margin was 31.7%, above our raised guidance. NFL Christmas Day games were watched by 52 million households globally on Netflix — a single-day streaming record. For 2026, we expect to add 30–35 million net subscribers and target an operating margin above 34%."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "spencer-neumann",
      "speaker_name": "Spencer Neumann",
      "speaker_role": "CFO",
      "timestamp": "00:18:00",
      "text": "Q4 revenue was $12.4 billion, up 16% year-over-year. Full-year revenue was $45.5 billion, up 15%. Operating income for Q4 was $2.3 billion and for the full year was $14.4 billion. For Q1 2026, we expect revenue of $11.1–11.5 billion and an operating margin of approximately 28%."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "operator",
      "speaker_name": "Operator",
      "speaker_role": "Operator",
      "timestamp": "00:36:00",
      "text": "Our next question comes from Mark Mahaney at Evercore ISI."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "analyst-mark-mahaney",
      "speaker_name": "Mark Mahaney",
      "speaker_role": "Analyst",
      "timestamp": "00:36:20",
      "text": "Spencer, 34% operating margin target for 2026 while adding 30–35 million subscribers — is that margin target dependent on advertising reaching a specific revenue threshold, or is it achievable on subscription economics alone?"
    }
  ],
